;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 2560w\" src=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/garden-explainer-tdf-gardens-extra2.jpg\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch3\u003e3. Work with your interiors\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFran Hale, of \u003ca href=\"https://www.peachygreen.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003ePeachy Green\u003c/a\u003e, says, ‘Choose beautiful sustainable materials that feel soft and luxurious underfoot and work with your interior surfaces and colours to bring cohesiveness and flow from indoors to out.’\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eInstall or hang lighting so it looks pretty when viewed from anywhere in the home.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003e4. Make space for entertaining\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCreate a welcoming space for entertaining with plenty of lovely, lush planting, Fran advises.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePrioritise comfortable seating arrangements, ambient lighting and a focal point like an outdoor fire or pizza oven to draw visitors outdoors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA barbecue for outdoor cooking is a necessity — build it in to save space if you can.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor smaller spaces, look for compact, moveable furniture that can be effortlessly rearranged to accommodate guests, and easily switched between relaxed lounge seating and a more structured dining setting.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"NaN\" height=\"NaN\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"50vw\" srcset=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra4.webp\u0026amp;w=384\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 384w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra4.webp\u0026amp;w=768\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 768w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra4.webp\u0026amp;w=1440\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1440w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra4.webp\u0026amp;w=1920\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1920w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra4.webp\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 2560w\" src=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra4.webp\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"NaN\" height=\"NaN\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"50vw\" srcset=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra3.webp\u0026amp;w=384\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 384w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra3.webp\u0026amp;w=768\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 768w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra3.webp\u0026amp;w=1440\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1440w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra3.webp\u0026amp;w=1920\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1920w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra3.webp\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 2560w\" src=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra3.webp\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"NaN\" height=\"NaN\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra7.webp\u0026amp;w=768\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 768w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra7.webp\u0026amp;w=1440\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1440w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra7.webp\u0026amp;w=1920\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1920w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra7.webp\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 2560w\" src=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra7.webp\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch3\u003e5. Less is more\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFran’s advice for small backyards is to avoid clutter and filling up the space too much.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e‘Tuck items such as bins, clotheslines, bikes, utility and service units down the side of the house, so the main courtyard or garden space can be all about beauty, ambience, great furniture and wonderful plants’, she says.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEnsure plant choices are the right size and shape for the space so they don’t grow too wide or tall.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003e6. Look beyond grass\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf having a lawn isn’t an option, there are some great ground cover alternatives that will provide the same lush green carpet effect.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eFran’s favourite plants to use as an alternative to grass:\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ci\u003eDichondra repens \u003c/i\u003e(kidneyweed)\u003cbr/\u003e\n\u003ci\u003eViola hederacea \u003c/i\u003e(native violet)\u003cbr/\u003e\n\u003ci\u003ePratia pedunculata \u003c/i\u003e(white star creeper)\u003cbr/\u003e\n\u003ci\u003eZoysia tenuifolia \u003c/i\u003e(no mow grass)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"NaN\" height=\"NaN\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"50vw\" srcset=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/garden-explainer-tdf-gardens7.jpg\u0026amp;w=384\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 384w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/garden-explainer-tdf-gardens7.jpg\u0026amp;w=768\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 768w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/garden-explainer-tdf-gardens7.jpg\u0026amp;w=1440\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1440w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/garden-explainer-tdf-gardens7.jpg\u0026amp;w=1920\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1920w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/garden-explainer-tdf-gardens7.jpg\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 2560w\" src=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/garden-explainer-tdf-gardens7.jpg\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"NaN\" height=\"NaN\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"50vw\" srcset=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/PeachyGreen-tdf-ditl5.jpg\u0026amp;w=384\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 384w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/PeachyGreen-tdf-ditl5.jpg\u0026amp;w=768\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 768w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/PeachyGreen-tdf-ditl5.jpg\u0026amp;w=1440\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1440w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/PeachyGreen-tdf-ditl5.jpg\u0026amp;w=1920\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1920w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/PeachyGreen-tdf-ditl5.jpg\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 2560w\" src=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/PeachyGreen-tdf-ditl5.jpg\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"NaN\" height=\"NaN\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"50vw\" srcset=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra5.webp\u0026amp;w=384\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 384w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra5.webp\u0026amp;w=768\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 768w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra5.webp\u0026amp;w=1440\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1440w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra5.webp\u0026amp;w=1920\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1920w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra5.webp\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 2560w\" src=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra5.webp\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"NaN\" height=\"NaN\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"50vw\" srcset=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra6.webp\u0026amp;w=384\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 384w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra6.webp\u0026amp;w=768\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 768w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra6.webp\u0026amp;w=1440\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1440w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra6.webp\u0026amp;w=1920\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 1920w, https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra6.webp\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp 2560w\" src=\"https://wsrv.nl/?url=https://thedesignfiles.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gardensexplainer-tdf-extra6.webp\u0026amp;w=2560\u0026amp;q=75\u0026amp;output=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch3\u003e7. Study your climate\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e‘One big problem small inner-city gardens face is limited space and sunlight,’ says Clea.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSoil quality poses another challenge; it might be compacted, polluted or there may be no soil at all.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThoughtful plant selection is key to success. Clea suggests choosing plants that thrive in your local climate, sun and soil condition to foster a biodiverse and pollinator-friendly environment.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003e8. Play with scale\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCreate depth and texture by layering plants of different heights and forms.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTall trees or shrubs can provide privacy and shade, while low-growing plants or ground covers can carpet walkways or fill gaps.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e‘A focal point, such as a sculpture or feature tree will add interest without taking up too much space,’ Clea suggests.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch3\u003eRecent Gardens\u003c/h3\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
